<promed@promed.org>
[Lymphatic filariasis is endemic in Thailand, and assessment by WHO of
the national control programme shows several constraints: low coverage
in mass chemotherapy due to side effects of DEC, and gaps in the
knowledge of the possibility of a zoonotic reservoir, among others.
<http://w3.whosea.org/lymphatic/thailand.htm>. - Mod.EP
[In southern Thailand, filariasis is caused by the nematode worm
_Brugia malayi_, which has a reservoir in cats, civet cats (_Viverra
tangalunga_) & monkeys. - Mod.JW
